added.title: Kabooms Part 1
added.description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

added.title: Kabooms Part 2
added.description: Inspired by the "Babies vs Dogs" movie, the Titans decide to make a big Hollywood film of their own.

added.title: I Used to Be a Peoples
added.description: Robin feels the other Titans are spending too much time together so he encourages them to spend some time alone.

added.title: Movie Night
added.description: It's Movie Night and the Titans have a hard time deciding who gets to choose which movie they watch.

added.title: Titan Saving Time
added.description: The Titans are determined to find out what happened to the missing 2'oclock hour during Daylight Saving Time.

added.title: Easter Creeps
added.description: It's Easter and the Tooth Fairy is trying to take over the holiday.

added.title: Beast Girl
added.description: As the Titans deal with Madame Rouge, Beast Boy is excited to meet his female counterpart Beast Girl.

added.title: Bro-Pocalypse
added.description: When the male Titans are injured, Raven and Starfire must become bros to stop the Bropocalypse.

added.title: The Fourth Wall
added.description: Control Freak informs the Titans that they are on a TV show he created and demands they earn him an award.

added.title: Two Parter Part 1
added.description: The Titans visit the Hall of Justice to use the pool, but then decide to check out the inside.

added.title: Two Parter Part 2
added.description: The Titans must save the members of the Justice League from the clutches of the supervillain Darkseid.

added.title: The Teen Titans Go Easter Holiday Classic
added.description: The Easter Bunny is missing, and it's up to the Titans to find him before Easter is ruined.

added.title: Who's Laughing Now
added.description: Beast Boy decides to find his spirit animal and joins a group of bears.

added.title: Ice Cave
added.description: Ralph takes over the cave and turns it into a snowy fortress where he reigns as king over the Bears and Charlie.

added.title: Hurricane Hal
added.description: A storm rolls in while the Bears are separated. Grizz looks after the Poppy Rangers. Panda is stuck with Charlie in his car. And Chloe and Ice Bear are in the city seeking a ride home.

added.title: I Am Ice Bear
added.description: After Ice Bear hits his head, Grizz and Panda notice him acting like a different person.

added.title: Go Fish
added.description: While on a fishing trip, the Bears get attacked by a giant legendary fish.

added.title: Family Troubles
added.description: Baby Grizz lives on the set of a sitcom in which he stars. But when a cooler kid joins the cast, Grizz feels threatened.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: The Island
added.description: While trying to sail to Japan, the Baby Bears get stranded on an island. Luckily, they meet Dave and Karla, who help with survival on the island while looking for an escape.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Pet Shop
added.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

added.title: Cupcake Job
added.description: When the Bears' beloved laptop breaks, they finally have the need to do something they've never done before: get jobs. Working at a trendy cupcake shop, the Bears find  that the working world is much tougher than they realized.

added.title: The Void
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin investigate a missing classmate, they discover a far greater mystery . . . about Elmore. Gumball and Darwin start noticing small details around Elmore High that don't add up. They come to the conclusion that Molly has disappeared, even though nobody else remembers her ever having existed. Mr Small confirms their suspicions and tells them that things are not always what they seem in Elmore. They set off on a quest to rescue Molly in an alternate dimension, and soon need rescuing themselves!

added.title: The Safety
added.description: Darwin watches a Health and Safety video and gets carried away. When Mr Small shows a health and safety video in class, Darwin becomes obsessed with the idea of keeping the Wattersons safe. He tries to protect them from the world around them and soon Darwin's over-protective control-freakery spreads to every corner of Elmore. The Wattersons have no choice but to overthrow his despotic regime.

added.title: The Society
added.description: Gumball is convinced there is a Secret Society in school and he wants in. Things aren't going Gumball's way at school so he assumes there must be a Secret Society that gives preferential treatment to its own members. He tries everything to uncover this non-existent society, making everyone's lives miserable in the process. Eventually, in an attempt to restore some peace, the pupils and teachers decide to give him exactly what he wants.

added.title: The Spoiler
added.description: Can Gumball and Darwin get through a whole week without somebody ruining the movie they're planning to see? Gumball and Darwin have spent all their pocket money, so will have to wait until the following weekend to see "The Screamening." It"s the scariest film of the year. The only problem is everyone else has seen it, and won't stop talking about it. Gumball is determined to avoid all spoilers. Will he succeed?

added.title: The Triangle
added.description: Gumball is jealous when Darwin discovers a hidden musical talent, and he may not be the only one. Darwin joins the school marching band, and his tin-whistle talent lands him the solo. Gumball misses having his friend to goof off with and tries to get rehearsal cancelled. So when Darwin's whistle is sabotaged nobody believes Gumball is innocent. Gumball, meanwhile, sets out to find the true culprit, or there may be no encore.

added.title: The Apology
added.description: For once in his life Gumball is the one who's owed an apology...from Ms Simian!

added.title: The Bet
added.description: When Bobert becomes Gumball's servant for a week, Gumball realizes robots obey everyone's command... even if that means destroying you!

added.title: The Authority
added.description: Granny JoJo's overprotective behavior puts the Wattersons in danger...from themselves.

added.title: The Finale
added.description: The Wattersons are surprised to discover that their past actions have consequences.

added.title: The Responsible
added.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

added.title: The Third
added.description: Gumball and Darwin spice up their friendship by introducing a third best friend.

added.title: The Robot
added.description: Gumball discovers that Bobert is planning to take over his identity and replace him!

added.title: The Secret
added.description: Gumball almost loses his mind trying to guess Darwin's secret.

added.title: The Sock
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are taught confusing lessons about honesty by the school councillor.

added.title: The Wand
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make their dad believe in magic again.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Double Hex
added.description: While bird watching at Pinnacles National Park, Gwen and Ben get into a competition of who can spot more birds first, but once a forest fire interrupts their fun, Team Tennyson must hurry if they are to save the bird population and discover who is behind the suspiciously growing fire: Hex!

added.title: Ben Again and Again
added.description: After Billy Billions' efforts to carve his face onto Mount Rushmore with a laser are thwarted by Ben, the billionaire brat turns his focus on removing Ben from the Omnitrix, but once he accidentally rips open a rift in space-time, the two must carefully navigate another timeline if they are to return to the present.

added.title: Drone On
added.description: Ben and Gwen are in a highly competitive paper airplane war, but when alien-tech drones bombard the Rustbucket, the cousins must work together to ground the aerial attack and find out who's behind it: the alien conqueror, Vilgax!

added.title: Dreamtime
added.description: After a series of reoccurring nightmares affect his sleep, Ben refuses to open up to Max and Gwen about what's bothering him, but once they realize Zombozo himself is behind it, Ben must accept Max and Gwen's help if they are going to put a stop to the terror.

added.title: Waterfilter
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: Adventures in Babysitting
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max meet a family that appears to be a mirror image of them, but when Max goes off on a hike with their matriarch, Maxine, Ben is forced to babysit Simon Sez, a brat with a Billy Billions designed backpack  that turns him into a formidable robot.

added.title: Steam is the Word
added.description: In the heart of Silicon Valley, Ben has to stop Victorian villain Steam Smythe from securing an epic power source sealed in a Tesla time capsule.

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: Council of the Creek
added.description: The circle game wreaks havoc on the Creek, so Craig forms a council to restore order.

added.title: Ferret Quest
added.description: The kids are on the search for an elusive ferret in the Creek.  Kelsey unites her friends Stacks and Wildernessa to find it, but worries they'd rather hangout with each other instead of her.

added.title: Into the Overpast
added.description: Craig and The Green Poncho travel to the Other Side of the Creek where Craig learns Green Poncho's shocking origin story.

added.title: Beyond the Rapids
added.description: Resident creek scientist Wren enlists Craig to voyage through dangerous waters in search of a path to the Ocean.

added.title: Sunday Clothes
added.description: JP dirties his last clean clothes and he must wear his Sunday best to the creek.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Kelsey Quest
added.description: Kelsey accepts a quest from the Elders of the Creek, but is she ready for her terrifying opponent?

added.title: JPony
added.description: JP decides to follow his heart and tries to join the Horse Girls.

added.title: The Climb
added.description: Craig's phone gets stuck in Mt. Sycamore, the tallest tree in the creek!

added.title: Germ Factory
added.description: After seeing Leshawna enjoying a sick day at home with ice cream and TV, Duncan convinces the other kids try to get sick too.

added.title: Fun Proof
added.description: Apple and Onion want to become this week's "Most Fun People".

added.title: Whale Spotting
added.description: Apple and Onion need to join an exclusive club to see a rare whale.

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: Apple and Onion must find a way to use Burger's trampoline without making him feel used.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple needs to acquire a lifetime supply of toilet paper to finish his modern art sculpture.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Apple tries to survive a weekend alone while taking care of Onion's plant.

added.title: Party Popper
added.description: Apple and Onion's party plans are interrupted by a grumpy guest.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears while trapped in a pet shop, so they can save French Fry from facing hers.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: The Great Bongo Heist
added.description: The boys forget to get Chata a gift for Abuela Day and in a panicked move, they pretend that the bongo drums they borrowed from Xochi are for her. Knowing they have to return the drums, Victor & Valentino pretend to be burglars to steal the bongos back.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: On Nagual Hill
added.description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

added.title: Dewey Wins
added.description: Steven helps Mayor Dewey run a difficult campaign.

added.title: Back to the Kindergarten
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Peridot try to spruce up the Kindergarten.

added.title: Can't Go Back
added.description: Ronaldo spots something mysterious on the moon, and Steven goes to investigate.

added.title: A Single Pale Rose
added.description: Steven helps Pearl find her phone.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: The Kindergarten Kid
added.description: Steven and the Gems deal with a monster problem.

added.title: The Zoo
added.description: Steven visits a special zoo.

added.title: The New Crystal Gems
added.description: Connie helps look after Beach City while Steven is busy.

added.title: The Good Lars
added.description: Steven, Lars and Sadie get invited to a party with the Cool Kids.

added.title: Together Breakfast
added.description: Steven tries to get the Gems to take part in his special breakfast tradition, but instead finds himself tumbling through the magical catacombs of the Crystal Gem's temple.

added.title: Watermelon Steven
added.description: Steven discovers a new power when he grows a patch of Steven-shaped watermelons!

added.title: Warp Tour
added.description: Steven thinks he sees something creepy traversing the warp streams and the Gems try to ease his paranoia.

added.title: The Test
added.description: Steven finds out that his mission to the Lunar Sea Spire was a test and demands a new one.

added.title: Winter Forecast
added.description: Steven has to get Connie home before it snows.

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: Breakup
added.description:
Feeling left out, Adorabat wishes Mao Mao and Badgerclops would spend less time with each other and more time with her. When she gets
what she wishes for and accidentally breaks up their friendship, only the secret of their past can bring them back together.

added.title: Popularity Conquest
added.description: When Mao Mao discovers that he is not as popular as Badgerclops and Adorabat, they decide to reinvent him as a kinder, cuddlier hero.

added.title: Sick Mao
added.description: When Mao Mao won't admit that he's sick, he puts the town in danger.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: The gang decide to compete in the annual Thumb War competition, but a surprise forces Mao Mao to deal with the unthinkable... losing.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: Always BMO Closing
added.description: BMO and Ice King hit the road as door to door salesmen and stumble upon an irresistible opportunity.

added.title: Bonnibel Bubblegum
added.description: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to harken back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

added.title: Jake the Starchild
added.description: In order to fulfill his grand destiny, Jake is spirited away by a strangely familiar shape-shifting alien.

added.title: Gumbaldia
added.description: Finn and Jake, as ambassadors of the Candy Kingdom, travel to a powerful new city-state in a last ditch effort to stave off war.

added.title: Finn the Human
added.description: After chasing the Lich through the portal, Finn and Jake meet a wishmaster named Prismo.

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: Jakesuit
added.description: Jake is sick and tired of Finn using his body as a suit of armor so he convinces Finn to trade places to show him how much it really stinks.

added.title: Earth & Water
added.description: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Flame Princess's fiery tendencies. When there's an emergency at the treehouse and Princess Bubblegum leaves Cinnamon Bun to watch Flame Princess, her experiment might literally backfire in her face.

added.title: James
added.description: Finn and Jake are excited when Princess Bubblegum invites them to help her collect samples in the Desert of Wonders. But when their vessel is attacked by nasty goo monsters, Finn and Jake start to think the mission has been sabotaged by Princess Bubblegum's robot helper James.

added.title: King Worm
added.description: Finn has a particularly vivid dream, and all of Ooo is in it or does he?

added.title: Lady & Peebles
added.description: Princess Bubblegum and Lady Rainicorn go on a quest to find Finn and Jake who are missing after fighting the Ice King.

added.title: Beautopia
added.description: Susan Strong returns to tell Finn and Jake that her world is in danger!

added.title: Jake vs. Me-Mow
added.description: Finn and Jake grapple with a tiny feline assassin.

added.title: Marceline's Closet
added.description: Finn and Jake spend a nerve-wracking afternoon trapped in Marceline's closet.

added.title: Loyalty to the King
added.description: There's a new "Nice King" in Ooo, and he looks kinda like someone else we know.

added.title: Brain Trust
added.description: Dr. Fox accidentally transports the gang inside her brain, where they must control her movements to complete a dangerous experiment.

added.title: Kitty & Hawk
added.description: When Puppycorn's favorite toy goes missing, Unikitty & Hawkodile team up to track down the thief, buddy-cop style! But when things get tough and the case goes cold, now it's not just their partnership on the line, but their friendship!

added.title: Bedtime Stories
added.description: When Puppycorn can't fall asleep, Dr. Fox uses an invention to bring classic bedtime stories to life. But the gang's presence leads to some surprising twists in these popular tales.

added.title: Dunklecorn
added.description: A mysterious relative, Uncle Donklecorn, shows up unexpectedly, claiming to be family. Hawkodile thinks it's just Master Frown and Brock in a donkey costume, trying to ruin things as usual, but Unikitty and Puppycorn are convinced Donklecorn is an old family member. Hawk follows his bodyguard senses and tries to prove that Donklecorn is a fake, until finally the real Master Frown and Brock show up and ruin things, just as he suspected they would. He admits he was wrong about Uncle Donklecorn, but all is forgiven and the friends dance it out together.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

added.title: Wishing Well
added.description: When Puppycorn uses a wishing well and it doesn't come true, Unikitty is shocked to discover the reason: all the wishes made over the years can't be granted because they're trapped at the bottom of the well (it's a dumb system.) She frees them to bring joy to the town… only to discover that they've gone a little bad after years trapped in a dark hole. Soon, they wish it would end!

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Unikitty News!
added.description: You're watching the Unikingdom News Show Super Good Morning Time Program Action Information Show, a variety news program put on (badly) by Unikitty and the gang: Hawkodile does the weather, Puppycorn does sports despite knowing none of the rules, Dr. Fox puts on a fun science-y cooking segment that goes awry, and Richard wants this to stop. Unikitty's got some hard hitting reporting and a big scoop after the break, if the studio survives that long!

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Kabums Part 1
added.description: Los Titanes están ansiosos por ver la versión cinematográfica de su programa favorito, "Bebés vs. perros", hasta que la presentación de la película hace que se vuelva superaburrida de ver. Para salvarla, los Titanes se meten en la película e interrumpen la charla con mucha acción fascinante.

added.title: Kabums Part 2
added.description: Inspirados por la película "Bebés vs. perros", los Titanes deciden hacer una gran película de Hollywood propia.

added.title: Yo Era Una Gente
added.description: Robin cree que los Titanes pasan demasiado tiempo juntos, así que los alienta a pasar un poco más de tiempo separados.

added.title: Chad and the Marathon
added.description: When Chad realizes his lazy habits might be rubbing off on Clarence, he decides to participate in the Aberdale Marathon. However, the athletic Chad doesn't know the first thing about being a runner, and must enlist the help of Clarence to train!

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: A Nightmare on Aberdale Street: Balance's Revenge
added.description: In this Halloween adventure, Clarence uses a special jack-o-lantern to enter the world of people's dreams. He discovers that something mysterious is causing his friends to have nightmares, and Clarence needs to stop it!

added.title: A Sumoful Mind
added.description: When Jeff realizes Sumo's new classes have been rubbing off on Sumo, he attempts to further foster this newfound intellectual Sumo! But will Clarence's lowbrow antics reverse Jeff's hard work?

added.title: Animal Day
added.description: Clarence feels the call of the wild - and decides to live a new life, free of the hustle and bustle of the modern world. Recruiting a few friends, Clarence sets out to find a new place to live his feral life, but quickly realizes he lacks some basic survival skills.

added.title: Raritos de Pascua
added.description: Llegó la Pascua y el Hada de los Dientes intenta apoderarse de la festividad.

added.title: We Are Heroes
added.description: KO struggles with his upgraded role as a member of the hero team.

added.title: Not So Secret Service
added.description: After Mojo Jojo's latest creation threatens to blast him into tiny bits, the Powerpuff Girls are forced to take Mojo in.

added.title: The Little Mer-Tiger
added.description: The origin of Tiger is told as a flashback.  As the legend goes, Tiger used to be a mermaid.  One day the evil ruler of the sea, Bubble Grandpa, demanded a hamburger and picked Tiger to retrieve it.  He used his magic sea powers to give Tiger legs and send her ashore.  But Tiger grew to love the land, and with the help of her new friend, Uncle Grandpa, defeated the evil sea ruler and got to keep her legs.

added.title: TKO Rules!
added.description: KO and TKO decide to swap places for the day.

added.title: Mojo the Great
added.description: In an effort to make himself great, Mojo steals the powers that makes the each of the Powerpuff girls the heroes they are.

added.title: Uncle Easter
added.description: The Easter Bunny, unable to fulfill his egg-delivering duties, has Uncle Grandpa fill in for him.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Whatever Happened to... Rippy Roo?
added.description: Rippy Roo visits the plaza.

added.title: Lame Station
added.description: Pizza Steve tries desperately to make the others in the RV interested in his new game console.

added.title: Largo
added.description: When a mysterious rain cloud plagues Townsville, Bubbles learns things aren't what they seem.

added.title: Ragnarock and Roll
added.description: When an ancient prophecy spells doom for Townsville, the girls must race to stop it.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: Gut Model
added.description: Muscle Man becomes a model.

added.title: Fists of Justice
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to do all of Skips' duties for the day.

added.title: Cueva Helada
added.description: Ralph se apodera de la cueva y la convierte en una fortaleza nevada, donde reina sobre los Osos y Charlie.

added.title: Diary
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to fix a lock on Margaret's diary before she gets back from a weekend trip.

added.title: Death Bear
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to get a picture in death bear's cage to impress Margaret and Eileen.

added.title: Fuzzy Dice
added.description: Everyone wants to give Pops some fuzzy dice for his birthday.

added.title: Huracan Hal
added.description: Se desata una tormenta y los Osos están en distintos lugares. Pardo cuida a las Guardabosques de la Amapola. Panda queda varado con Charlie en su auto. Y Chloe y Polar están en la ciudad, buscando alguien que los lleve a su casa.

added.title: Yo soy Polar
added.description: Cuando Polar se golpea la cabeza, Pardo y Panda se dan cuenta de que su comportamiento cambia.

added.title: De Pesca
added.description: Durante un viaje de pesca, los osos son atacados por un enorme pez legendario.

added.title: Problemas Familiares
added.description: Pardo bebé vive en el set de filmación de una comedia que protagoniza. Pero cuando llega un niño con más onda al elenco, Pardo se siente amenazado.

added.title: Batalla en El Biggie Box
added.description: Ben y Billy Billions se enfrentan por un set de sumo exclusivo que se vende únicamente en el centro comercial más grande del mundo, isolo para descubrir que Simon Sez, de apenas seis años, lo compró primero! Así se desata una batalla dentro de una tienda que parece tenerlo todo excepto una salida fácil de encontrar.

added.title: Doble Hex
added.description: Mientras observan aves en el Parque Nacional Pinnacles, Gwen y Ben comienzan a competir para ver quién puede avistar más aves primero. Pero cuando el fuego del bosque interrumpe su diversión, el equipo Tennyson debe darse prisa para salvar a la población de aves y descubrir quién está detrás del fuego que crece sospechosamente: iHex!

added.title: Ben una y otra vez
added.description: Cuando los esfuerzos de Billy Billiones por tallar su cara en el Monte Rushmore con un láser se ven frustrados por Ben, el malcriado multimillonario se concentra en sacar a Ben del Omnitrix. Pero cuando, por accidente, abre una grieta espacio-temporal, ambos deben navegar con cuidado por otra línea de tiempo si quieren regresar al presente.

added.title: Vuela Dron
added.description: Ben y Gwen se enfrentan en una guerra de avioncitos de papel sumamente competitiva. Pero cuando unos drones con tecnología alienígena bombardean el Rustbucket, los primos deben trabajar juntos para derribar el ataque aéreo y descubrir quién está detrás de eso: iVilgax, el conquistador extraterrestre!

added.title: Project Ray Way
added.description: When Raymond starts his own fashion line, Rad and Drupe decide to make something even better.

added.title: Tiempo de Sonar
added.description: Después de una serie de pesadillas recurrentes que afectan su sueño, Ben se niega a contarles a Max y Gwen lo que le molesta. Pero una vez que se dan cuenta de que el propio Zombozo está detrás de las pesadillas, Ben debe aceptar la ayuda de Max y Gwen si quieren ponerle fin al terror.

added.title: A Jolt from the Past
added.description: Alien pests from Ben's youth come back, but now they need Ben's help. (Introducing Fistrick, & new Ben alien Gravattack.)

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Pozo de los deseos
added.description: Cuando Puppycorn utiliza una fuente de los deseos y su deseo no se hace realidad, Unikitty se sorprende al descubrir la razón: todos los deseos realizados a lo largo de los años no se pueden cumplir porque están atrapados en el fondo de la fuente (es un sistema tonto). Unikitty los libera para que traigan alegría a la ciudad, y así descubre que se echaron a perder un poco después de años atrapados en un agujero oscuro. iPronto todos desearán que todo se termine!

added.title: La Maldicion
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP entran en conflicto con unas brujas adolescentes deshonestas, ique les lanzan una maldición! iQué adolescentes malvadas!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El futuro es de Carton
added.description: Los niños conocen a un excéntrico Creador de Cartón que invita a Craig a ayudarlo a terminar su obra maestra.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Zona
added.description: A Unikitty le cuesta mantener la calma cuando juega a videojuegos y entra en La Zona, a diferencia de Puppycorn, su hermano menor. Pero un repentino accidente de laboratorio destroza su consola y ahora, para su sorpresa, el castillo se bloquea como un videojuego del mundo real, icon sus amigos como jugadores! ¿Podrá Unikitty salvar a sus amigos y dominar La Zona antes de que termine el juego?

added.title: Demasiados Unikitties
added.description: Unikitty llega a la conclusión de que todo el mundo sería mucho más feliz si pensara como ella, iy tal vez pueda lograrlo con la ayuda de la Dra. Fox! Unikitty copia sus ondas cerebrales en todos sus amigos y los Unikittyfica, para que todos puedan ser siempre positivos. Pero pronto, Unikitty se da cuenta de que puede haber un exceso de "buena princesa".

added.title: Freezer Burn
added.description: Batman and Firestorm team up to fight their respective cold villains, Mr. Freeze and Killer Frost. Complications arise when Firestorm's infatuation for the wily Ms. Frost gets the best of him.

added.title: Noticias Unikitty
added.description: Estás viendo el programa de noticias del Unireino Super Good Morning Time Action Information Show, un programa de noticias variadas realizado (mal) por Unikitty y la banda: Hawkodile se encarga del clima, Puppycorn habla deportes, a pesar de no saber ninguna de las reglas, la Dra. Fox tiene un divertido segmento de cocina científica que sale mal, y Richard quiere que el programa deje de emitirse. Unikitty tiene un reportaje contundente y una gran primicia después de la pausa, isi el estudio sobrevive tanto tiempo!

added.title: Inside Job
added.description: In a "Fantastic Voyage" like adventure, Atom shrinks Batman and Wonder Woman so they can enter Superman's bloodstream and destroy a lethal nanite virus.

added.title: Double Cross
added.description: Batman has Plastic Man disguise himself as Two-Face in order to set a trap for Deadshot. Unfortunately things get complicated when the real Two-Face escapes custody.

added.title: A escalar
added.description: iEl teléfono de Craig se atasca en el Monte Sicomoro, el árbol más alto del Arroyo!
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Battle for the Bottled City
added.description: Atom shrinks Superman so he can visit his fellow Kryptonians in the bottled city of Kandor. Soon after, Brainiac attacks and takes off with the bottle. Atom is forced to take control of one of Superman's damaged robots in order to follow after Brainiac and retrieve the city.

added.title: Garden of Evil
added.description: Poison Ivy takes control of Swamp Thing using his vegetative powers to overwhelm Gotham with dangerous plants.

added.title: Sabro Atraco
added.description: Richard preparó uno de los postres más sabrosos de todos los tiempos, pero lo cerró con llave hasta que los amigos terminen su cena aburrida. Esto no va a seguir así. Para organizar un atraco, Unikitty organiza a sus amigos como un comité de expertos para entrar, salir y comer ese sabroso bocadillo sin que Richard lo sepa. Pero este atraco tiene un traspié. ¿Podrán los amigos llevarse el pastel?

added.title: La Aventura Perfecta
added.description: Cuando a Mao Mao se le antoja vivir la aventura perfecta, Adorabat dice una mentira piadosa.

added.title: Bismuto Casual
added.description: Perla invita a Bismuto a la pista de patinaje para darle una lección sobre cómo forjar relaciones humanas.

added.title: En Suenos
added.description: Los sueños de Steven comienzan a transmitirse en el televisor de su dormitorio.

added.title: Te Quiero Mao Mao
added.description: Un solitario explosivo y su mejor amigo holgazán se desvían del viaje que los llevará a convertirse en leyenda y descubren que su historia apenas comienza.

added.title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
added.description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: The Headsucker's Moxy/Equal Fights
added.description: The Headsucker's Moxy: There's a mysterious villain in town who's sucking pertinent information from the brains of powerful people and committing crimes. How do the girls trap this sucker before his next victim is drained?/Equal Fights: When the girls try to catch a local female villain, she tells them that as women they've got to stick together. It's up to the women of Townsville to teach our heroines the true meaning of equality.

added.title: Hot Air Buffoon/Ploys R' Us
added.description: Hot Air Buffoon: The Mayor realizes the girls are doing all the work in his city for him. So he mans a hot air balloon and starts fighting crime the old-fashioned way./Ploys R' Us: The girls wake up to find their room filled with toys. They soon figure out that the Professor has been sleepwalking and stealing. Instead of reporting it, the girls take advantage of the situation.

added.title: Gettin' Twiggy with It/Cop Out
added.description: Getting' Twiggy with It: Mitch takes Twiggy, the class hamster, home for the weekend. But when Mitch flushes Twiggy down the toilet, he emerges bigger and badder than ever./Cop Out: A lazy Townsville cop gets fired and blames the girls for saving the day too often, thereby stealing his job. Now, it's payback time and he has the perfect plan to stop those pint-size punks.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: En la colina Nahual
added.description: Vic y Val se apoderan de la colina de un bosque y construyen un tobogán de agua épico que perturba a las plantas y animales que solían habitar allí. Pero cuando un nahual (un humano con el poder de transformarse en animales) transforma a Vic en un pollo y a Val en un burro, ambos aprenden a empatizar con los animales y a entender el mundo un poco más.

added.title: Plaza Alone
added.description: It's KO's birthday, and Rad and Enid want to make sure everything goes perfectly.

added.title: All in the Villainy
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid are confused to find the villains are more interested in battling each other than them.

added.title: I Am Jethro
added.description: When a different kind of Jethro rolls off the assembly line, the plaza is in for some surprises.

added.title: KO's Health Week
added.description: KO spends a week dispensing healthy tips to everyone in the plaza.

added.title: Mystery Science Fair 201X
added.description: KO helps Dendy with her science fair project.

added.title: RMS & Brandon's First Episode
added.description: A Real Magic Skeleton discovers a new job opportunity.

added.title: Lad & Logic
added.description: KO learns the story of how Mr. Logic came to the plaza.

added.title: OK Dendy
added.description: Dendy fills in for KO at the bodega.

added.title: Let's Not Be Skeletons
added.description: When a charismatic huckster shows up to the plaza, the product he's selling turns everything upside down.

added.title: Hope This Flies
added.description: Rad attempts to upgrade his van and make it fly.

added.title: Cloris
added.description: When Clarence befriends an aging woman at the local retirement home, he's determined to remind her of her old self in order to convert the grumpy granny to his fun loving ways.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Belson's Backpack
added.description: After an accidental backpack swap, Clarence discovers that Belson is hiding an artistic side and attempts to foster Belson's creativity.

added.title: Motel
added.description: Following an insect mishap Clarence's house needs to be fumigated forcing Mary, Chad, and Clarence into a motel. In the meantime, Clarence and Chad learn a bit about responsibility while Mary contemplates a life of letting go.

added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise.

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Belson's Sleepover
added.description: Belson invites Clarence and friends to a sleepover party, with a catch: whoever can survive the night's pranks and scares will win Belson's old Acedia game system!

added.title: Goldfish Follies
added.description: Clarence buys a goldfish, but when the goldfish bag breaks before he can get home, Clarence must keep his new friend out of harms way and get him back into water before it's too late.

added.title: Chimney
added.description: While playing in the woods the boys befriend a wild dog, bring it home and name it Chimney. When the boys find themselves trapped in a well, the new pup is their only hope for escape.

added.title: Detention
added.description: After Clarence discovers that Mr. Reese falls asleep during detention when given a doughnut, it becomes the spot to be during recess. When Jeff gets wind of it he transforms it from a fun hang out spot to a too-cool-for-school club.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: Beat Your Greens/Down N' Dirty
added.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

added.title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
added.description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Birthday Bash/Too Pooped to Puff
added.description: Birthday Bash: It's the girls birthday and some special presents have arrived from the girls' main enemies. Can they destroy these evil gifts without destroying their party?/Too Pooped to Puff: The girls become exhausted when the town begins to over use them. They go on strike and end up teaching the townspeople how to fend for themselves.

added.title: Paste Makes Waste/Ice Sore
added.description: Paste Makes Waste: When Buttercup's taunting turns paste-eating classmate Elmer Sglue into a destructive Paste Monster, she gets out of a sticky situation by doing something against her tough nature, apologizing./Ice Sore: During a heat wave, Blossom discovers that she has a new power: ice breath. But when she doesn't use her new gift wisely, she gets a chilly reception from her sisters.

added.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
added.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

added.title: Bliss Reminisce
added.description: The Girls learn Bliss' backstory from the Professor, Mojo Jojo, and Bliss herself.

added.title: Breaking Bliss
added.description: When Bliss struggles to control her powers an evil force arises to take advantage.

added.title: A Slight Hiccup
added.description: The Girls must overcome their supersonic hiccups to stop the Gnat's latest evil plan!

added.title: The Stayover
added.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

added.title: Cheep Thrills
added.description: After finding a baby monster in the park, Bubbles insists on adopting it without considering the consequences!

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: The Squashening
added.description: To escape a monster, the girls have to tell him a scary story.

added.title: Dizzy
added.description: M and R help Pops get over his fear of public speaking.

added.title: Brain Eraser
added.description: Benson gets demoted and has to work with Mordecai and Rigby.

added.title: Benson Be Gone
added.description: Mordecai sees Pops naked and goes on a quest to unsee what he has seen.

added.title: But I Have a Receipt
added.description: When a bad game ruins game night, M & R attempt to return it to a not-so-pleasant store manager.

added.title: Do Me a Solid
added.description: Mordecai owes Rigby big time when he agrees to go on a double date with him.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Death Punchies
added.description: Rigby learns an ultimate karate move and becomes the bully of the park.

added.title: Prank Callers
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby try and prank the Master Prank Caller to be the best prank callers. The MPC sends them back to 1982.

added.title: Mordecai and the Rigbys
added.description: After lying about having an awesome band, Mordecai and Rigby must get help from their future selves in order to learn how to play in time for the battle of the bands.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Side Effects
added.description: Ben catches a cold and the symptoms wreak havoc on his alien heroes. To make matters even worse, he has to battle a creature made from cockroaches.

added.title: Tummy Trouble
added.description: When the Incursean armada kidnaps the Gourmand Queen, Ben and Rook must get the warring Gormand factions to work together to save her and stop the Incursean invasion.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: While You Were Away
added.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
added.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 2
added.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

added.title: Vreedlemania
added.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

added.title: Third Time's a Charm
added.description: Charmaster returns to exact her revenge on Gwendolyn once and for all.

added.title: The Trouble with Truth
added.description: The JLA find themselves in danger of losing Wonder Woman when the goddess Athena comes to Earth with an offer Diana can't refuse, filling the position of the Goddess of Truth on Mt. Olympus.

added.title: Dewey gana
added.description: Steven ayuda al alcalde Dewey a llevar adelante una campaña difícil.

added.title: De regreso a la guarderia
added.description: Steven, Amatista y Peridot intentan embellecer la guardería.

added.title: No puedo regresar
added.description: Ronaldo divisa algo misterioso en la luna, y Steven sale a investigar.

added.title: Una sola rosa palida
added.description: Steven ayuda a Perla a encontrar su teléfono.

added.title: Escapismo
added.description: Steven usa sus poderes psíquicos para conseguir ayuda.

added.title: Cambia de Parecer
added.description: Steven se enfrenta al mayor desafío de su vida.

added.title: El Nino de la Guarderia
added.description: Steven y las Gemas se enfrentan a un problema monstruoso.

added.title: Noche de Pelicula
added.description: Llegó la Noche de las Películas, y a los Titanes les cuesta decidir a quién le toca elegir qué película mirar.

added.title: El Horario de Verano Titan
added.description: Los Titanes están decididos a descubrir qué le sucedió a las dos de la tarde, la hora que se perdió durante el horario de verano.

added.title: Chica Bestia
added.description: Mientras los Titanes se enfrentan a Madame Rouge, Chico Bestia está entusiasmado por conocer a Chica Bestia, su equivalente femenina.

added.title: Hermano-lipsis
added.description: Cuando los chicos están heridos, Raven y Starfire deben convertirse en "hermanos" para detener el Hermano-lipsis.

added.title: Aguafiestas
added.description: Ben ignora completamente a Gwen cuando van a un centro de diversión familiar. Mientras tanto, Frightwig empuja a Zombozo a una vida de crímenes luego de que este termina convertido en un payaso para fiestas. iAhora, Zombozo y Ben deben aprender que no deberías ignorar a tus amigos!

added.title: Dales aire y dejalos salir
added.description: En la granja eólica de Mojave, Gwen y Max intentan enderezar las locas ideas de Ben sobre como funciona el viento. Pero cuando encuentran a los Climáticos usando las imponentes turbinas para sus viles objetivos, ¿podrá Ben aceptar los hechos a tiempo para derrotarlos?

added.title: Jacob del Arroyo
added.description: Un terrible corte de cabello obliga a Craig a visitar el Arroyo de encubierto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kitty y Halcon: Protectores de la Ley
added.description: Cuando el juguete favorito de Perricornio desaparece, Unikitty y Halcondrilo se unen para localizar al ladrón, ial estilo socios policías! Pero cuando las cosas se ponen difíciles y el caso no se resuelve, ya no es solo su sociedad la que está en juego, sino también su amistad.

added.title: El consejo del Arroyo

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Triquicornio
added.description: Un misterioso pariente, el tío Triquicornio, aparece inesperadamente asegurando ser de la familia. Halcondrilo cree que solo son Master Frown y Brock en un disfraz de burro tratando de arruinar las cosas, pero Unikitty y Perricornio están convencidos de que Triquicornio en un viejo miembro de la familia. Halcondrilo sigue sus instintos de guardaespaldas e intenta probar que Triquicornio es un impostor.

added.title: Mi Villana Familia

added.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
added.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

added.title: Dolores del crecimiento
added.description: Perricornio está cansado de que Unikitty siempre lo ayude y ya no quiere ser el hermano pequeño, así que usa un poco del dulce de crecimiento de la Dra. Fox para ser más grande que Unikitty.

added.title: La busqueda del huron
added.description: Los chicos salen en busca de un escurridizo hurón en el Arroyo. Kelsey se une junto a sus amigas Stacks y Salvajessa para encontrarlo, pero le preocupa que ellas prefieran pasar tiempo juntas entre sí que con ella.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Hechicero Calavera
added.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Juicio de Mino
added.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

added.title: Al pasado por el puente
added.description: Craig y el Poncho Verde viajan al otro lado del Arroyo, donde Craig conoce la impactante historia del origen del Poncho Verde.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Gran Caida
added.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

added.title: Plaza Abandonada
added.description: Es el cumpleaños de KO, y Rad y Enid quieren asegurarse de que todo salga a la perfección.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La Reina de los Munces
added.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

added.title: Pequena Escuela Madre
added.description: Bienvenidos a la Pequeña Escuela Madre, un lugar en la Tierra donde Gemas de todo el universo pueden aprender a vivir juntas pacíficamente. Pero hay una Gema que se rehúsa a asistir.

added.title: Consejos
added.description: Amatista ha estado ayudando a las Gemas de Pequeña Escuela Madre a encontrar trabajo, pero Steven no está seguro de su enfoque.

added.title: Filtro Acuatico
added.description: El viaje de Ben, Gwen y Max a las Cataratas del Niágara se ve interrumpido por los horribles Hydromanders: unas criaturas que los amenazan a ellos y a los demás turistas.

added.title: Video Viral
added.description: Los Osos creen que son capaces de convertirse en estrellas en un video viral, pero cuando Nom-Nom decide que eso no va a suceder, Pardo se mete en la limosina del koala con el objetivo de hacerlo cambiar de opinión.

added.title: El Lider Del Ring
added.description: Cuando Ben tiene una racha ganadora en un videojuego, se le ocurre una idea para ganar un partido real de lucha, hasta que un luchador intimidante decide convertirlo en un verdadero desafío.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Sobreviviendo A La Tormenta
added.description: El campamento de Ben y Gwen se ve interrumpido por los gélidos Weatherheads -Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o-, pero un Omnitrix que funciona mal y dispara un montón de extraterrestres podría no ser un pronóstico de éxito.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: Azulejo
added.description: Steven cuestiona los motivos de una misteriosa fusión que de repente se presenta en su casa.

added.title: Osos Cotidianos
added.description: Hoy es un día normal para los Osos. Eso significa que Ice se pelea con Roomba, que la vida de Panda queda patas arriba cuando un ratón invade su habitación y que Pardo queda varado en un árbol. Ya saben, las típicas cosas que les suceden a los osos.

added.title: Toma 10
added.description: Mientras Ben intenta rodar su propia película independiente, por accidente libera a una pandilla de insectos y, cuando la lucha se traslada a su guarida oculta, Ben debe enfrentarse a su líder narcisista: La Hormiga Reina.

added.title: Ropa Dominguera
added.description: JP ensucia su última ropa limpia y debe ponerse su mejor ropa de domingo para ir al arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Shhh
added.description: Mientras Ben se relaja en un monasterio con una política de silencio, no puede quedarse callado y, por accidente, despierta a un peligroso Dragón oculto en una recámara secreta bajo los salones sagrados...una tarea que podría ser demasiado para manejar, iincluso para Diamante!

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: Cuando, luego de un accidente reciente, Nom Nom aparece en la entrada de la casa de los Osos, desaliñado y destronado de su puesto como la estrella más tierna de Internet de la historia, consigue la ayuda de los Osos para tratar de recuperar su título.

added.title: Fabrica de germenes
added.description: Después de ver a Leshawna disfrutar de un día enferma en casa con helado y TV, Duncan convence a los otros chicos de que traten de enfermarse.

added.title: Rebelion En La Granja
added.description: Ben encuentra el laboratorio secreto del Doctor Ánimo -ahora gobernado por los alfas, sus mutantes superiores- y debe ayudar a los animales inferiores mientras está atrapado en forma de Insectoide.

added.title: Aventuras Cuidando Ninos
added.description: Ben, Gwen y Max se encuentran con una familia que parece ser un reflejo de ellos. Pero cuando Max sale a caminar con su matriarca, Maxine, Ben se ve obligado a cuidar a Simon Sez, un malcriado con una mochila diseñada por Billy Billones, que lo convierte en un robot formidable.

added.title: Perdidos en la Cloaca
added.description: Craig acepta ayudar a la Reina de las Alcantarillas a trazar el mapa de las alcantarillas, pero rápidamente se encuentra en una situación que lo supera.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Vapor Es La Palabra
added.description: En el corazón de Silicon Valley, Ben debe impedir que Vapor Smythe, el villano victoriano, consiga una fuente de poder épica sellada en una cápsula del tiempo diseñada por Tesla.

added.title: La Camada
added.description: La determinación de Craig de conseguirle a su abuelo un caparazón de cigarra hace que él, Kelsey y JP queden atrapados en su tronco.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Todo Mojado
added.description: Nadie le cree a Ben cuando insiste en que uno de los demás clientes que aguarda en la fila del parque acuático es la malvada Frightwig disfrazada de niña común. Por eso, Ben debe demostrar que dice la verdad mientras protege a los asistentes al parque del plan maestro de la villana: idestruir el parque con su propia presión acuática!

added.title: La aventura de Kelsey

added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Manana Es Hoy

Solo la devoción de Max por su ídolo de la infancia y la fe de Ben en los sueños puede salvar el mañana...ihoy mismo!

added.title: J-Pony
added.description: JP decide seguir su corazón y trata de unirse a las Chicas Ecuestres.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Tienda De Mascotas

Luego de un altercado con el equipo que filmaba un video absolutamente conmovedor de adopción de animales, los Osos por poco aprovechan la oportunidad de encontrar hogares alejados uno del otro.

added.title: La Tienda De Cupcakes
